The paper proposes a method for accelerating the training of Graph Convolutional Networks (GCNs) on large-scale graphs. This falls under the category of machine learning, specifically representation learning, which is covered by cs.LG. The paper also discusses the use of skip connections, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. Additionally, the proposed method involves variance reduction, which is a common technique in optimization and reinforcement learning, covered by cs.AI and cs.SI.
